The paper deals with a security mechanism to defend against colluding adversaries in peer-to-peer networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The mechanism involves the use of bandwidth puzzles, which are a form of distributed computing (cs.DC) and network protocols (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of the performance of the mechanism, which can be seen as a form of data analysis (cs.DS) and system optimization (cs.SY).
